query.result:
76 "I do not know," I replied to him, "how long I will live;
77 but my return will not be so soon
78 that I will not first be ready to go;

79 because the place where I was put to live
80 is losing more and more of its goodness every day,
81 and seems destined for a sad ruin."

112 Then she departed, as if having changed her mind;
113 and we came to the great tree now,
114 which rejects so many prayers and tears.

118 Someone was saying this among the leaves;
119 so Virgil, Statius, and I, close together,
120 went on along the side that rises.

